---
By: John Chrysostom
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 90
    Verse: 7
Tags:
  - Death
---
Death is to put off a garment. For the body is about the soul as a garment;
and after laying this aside for a short time by means of death, we shall
resume it again with the more splendor.
